sophy of Technoscience -- tIhdeology -- tForty Years in the Wilderness -- tSelect Bibliography -- tContributors -- tName Index0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aPostphenomenology is the first book devoted exclusively to the interpretation and advancement of prominent phenomenologist Don Ihde's landmark contributions to history, philosophy, sociology, science, sound studies, and technology studies. Ihde has made a direct and lasting impact on the study of technological experience across the disciplines and acquired an international following of diverse scholars along the way, many of whom contribute to Postphenomenology, including Albert Borgmann, who characterizes Ihde as being "among the most interesting and provocative contemporary American philosophers." The contributors situate, assess, and apply Ihde's philosophy with respect to the primary themes that his oeuvre emphasizes. They not only clarify Ihde's work, but also make significant contributions to the philosophy of technology, phenomenology, hermeneutics, and the philosophy of science. A comprehensive response from Ihde concludes the volume.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh1 aBorgmann, Albert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCohen, Richard A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrease, Robert P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeenberg, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGalison, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaraway, Donna J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIhde, Don, 